What was your sound source?

On Jun 11, 2007, at 6:40 AM, RetroCom wrote:

&gt;
&gt; I&#39;ve been testing an optical link design that replaces a normal  
&gt; microphone. The link consists of a red LED coupled to the sound  
&gt; source (EVP Maker or Linear radio  sweep) and the resultant  
&gt; modulated light is picked up by a photomultiplier tube.  The output  
&gt; of the tube is recorded on a VHS VCR (analog). Here&#39;s a couple  
&gt; examples from the session using EVP maker.
